15/10/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A new poll finds 50 per cent of Croatians are undecided about who they will support in next month's general election.
The survey, conducted by GfK Market Research Centre, asked respondents which party they would back in the coming vote.
Just over 50 per cent said they were not sure, 30 per cent knew for sure, while 16 per cent said they would not vote.
A total of 1,000 respondents participated in the poll, conducted at the end of September.
(HINA - 14/10/03)
